titleCaptionTranslation.workCaption:
Analog watercolor illustration, my first as an adult.

Nagi-chan from "Tea Boys in Wonderland" works part-time at her grandmother's tea house.

This is the first time I used transparent watercolor, and I used only one color of Schmincke's Buff Titanium.

It is the most expensive paint I have. ......:( ;-):.

The line drawing is a Copic multiliner.
The third one was scanned with a 7-Eleven multi-copier and the colors were adjusted.
I have also published an entire article about my illustration work on FANBOX.
Please take a look if you are interested.

April 2025.
